Thousands of mourners have been queuing since Saturday to view the body of the former president, who died last week at the age of 95.Â Moi's body has been lying in state since Saturday. President Uhuru Kenyatta and former President, Mwai Kibaki, who succeeded Moi in 2002, have viewed the body. Kenyans over the weekend queued to view Moi's body and more are expected on Monday being the last day of public viewing. A funeral service is scheduled for Tuesday at the Nyayo Stadium in the capital, Nairobi. Several heads of state have been reported to have confirmed attendance.

